cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.CE

The paper discusses challenges in cellular network architecture for 5G and proposes a solution called IsoRAN that provides isolation and scaling. This involves virtualization of the user level data plane in the Cloud Radio Access Network (CRAN) architecture. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the proposed solution involves distributed processing, cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as the paper discusses hardware efficiency, cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the solution involves meeting Service Level Agreements (SLAs), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as the paper discusses simulations and cost reduction.
